Splunk Universal Forwarder Installation (Main Windows Machine)
Step 1: Download Splunk Universal Forwarder

Visit the official Splunk Universal Forwarder download page:

https://www.splunk.com/en_us/download/universal-forwarder.html

Download the Windows 64-bit Universal Forwarder installer.

Step 2: Install Splunk Universal Forwarder
Open the downloaded installer.
Accept the license agreement.
Select the installation directory.
Enter administrator credentials when prompted.
Complete the installation process.
Step 3: Configure Forwarding Server

During installation, specify the Splunk server receiving port:

<Splunk_Server_IP>:9997

Example:

192.168.81.1:9997

This allows the Universal Forwarder to send logs to the Splunk Enterprise server.

Step 4: Verify Installation

Open Command Prompt as Administrator and navigate to:

C:\Program Files\SplunkUniversalForwarder\bin

Run:

splunk status

Expected Output:

splunkd is running
Outcome

Splunk Universal Forwarder is successfully installed and configured to forward Windows system logs and security events to the Splunk Enterprise server for centralized monitoring and analysis.
